&lt;p&gt;The land is flat, save for occasional dips and inclines while sloping gently downward toward Lake Ontario, due north. Wooded areas are mostly privately owned—with young, stick-like trees and densely packed shrubbery. All between and beyond the interstices of suburban development.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that there are scenes of visual intrigue to be had here, if you have a feel for subtlety.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/rural/91730029.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;barns and silo&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Ramshackle barns and a silo sit proud atop a gentle hill at a cattle farm. Newer facility just behind them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/water/afternooncreek.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;woodsy creek in the afternoon light&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;One of many creeks that flow north and join together before draining into Lake Ontario.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/rural/winterlakeorchard1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;snow-covered dormant apple orchard on the Lake Ontario coastline&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Dormant apple orchard. There’s a sliver of Lake Ontario on the horizon.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/rural/appleblossoms.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;blooming apple orchard along Erie Canal&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Blooming apple orchard along the Erie Canal.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/rural/2-1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;sunrise and fog over field&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Dips and and open fields hold the morning fog of spring and autumn.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/rural/2020_0703_03025500-01.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;clearing trees around the farm&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Spring cleaning.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/photos/rural/2020_0703_03161100-02.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;four horses out to pasture&quot; /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Four horses out to pasture.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

